The best steak I've ever eaten was consumed at this fine establishment.  I don't know a whole lot about steaks, I'm definitely no meat expert, but I've had plenty of them in my time.  I love steaks and I can say without a doubt that Harris' knows what they are doing.  They keep it simple and the way any good steak should be cooked: with some salt and pepper and NOTHING ELSE.  No fancy sauces or reduction mumbo-jumbo.  All you get is perfectly (I don't use that term lightly) cooked aged beef that melts in your mouth.  The taste is apparent and the quality is unrivaled.
